A Chinese newspaper, which had requested the release of a reporter on the title page was been charged with defamation, should be reformed, said a press regulator.
The Guangzhou-based new express had printed a rare public call for the release of the journalists Chen Yongzhou.
But later, Chen admitted on television that he had accepted bribes to falsify reports on a part of State owned company.
Now, the new express of a "comprehensive rectification" will undergo, the regulator said.
The "Rektifizierunganordnung" was issued by the authority for press and publications, radio, film and television in Guangdong.
Preliminary investigation revealed that the new Express, to the Yangcheng evening news group is one between September 2012 and August 2013 published several inaccurate reports about the listed company of Zoomlion had.
"The editorial management of the new Express was disorganized," announced the regulatory authority in a statement.
She said it decided "to impose an administrative penalty for Chen Yongzhou and to withdraw from its reporter license it".
There is also "the Yangcheng evening news group instructed to undertake a complete rectification of the new express and recommended to determine the relevant charge at the new express and immediately to check the management team of the new Express."
